text: Finally, a superhero film that looks like corny fun. Haven't seen one of them in a while. (Guardians of the galaxy doesn't count to me, because they aren't really superheroes, so it feels more like a Star Wars-y thing that got shoved into the superhero category because it's owned by Marvel.)  It feels weird that I even crave corny fun, but all the Marvel and DC films feel so serious and I crave variety above everything, so even something corny and dumb feels refreshing. I don't care much for superheroes, but I just feel weary from a decade of blockbusters being nothing but superhero films... Besides, I am looking forward to this; I need something to balance out EndGame.

text: I don't know, the humor isn't doing it for me, it seems to be completely reliant on how much of a dumbass the main character is. I'm pretty sure the actual 10-year-old Billy Batson was 100% less of a douche than this 15-year-old. The whole point of Shazam choosing him was because he was innocent but capable of using the powers properly. Here, it seems like they're trying to conflate "innocent" with "dumbass." Also, advanced age with senility, while making a random teenager act as the moral arbiter for Captain Marvel because we can't possibly have a competent parental figure in his life.

text: I don't understand why comic book "fans" force themselves into an ultimatum. Let's just celebrate the fact that we live in the golden age of comic book film adaptation and stop constantly comparing dick sizes. We're all allowed to like what we like and dislike what we don't, but there's no need to act so damn childish. No one wins from that scenario. What's so ridiculous is comic book fans have more in common with each other than they do the average person; we all share the love of fantastical superheroes donned in tights and capes drawn in little colorful boxes on a thin piece of paper, yet rather than acknowledge how similar our fandoms are, we continue to draw useless lines in the sand and argue vehemently over silly minutiae. It's just pointless. Live and let live.

text: First Aquaman, now Shazam. I think WB has finally learned to butt the fuck out cause they know shit about DC and just wanted another MCU.  But now we're really getting stories that ARE DC and they feel unraped by executive decissions.   I wish they'd learned this sooner. We wouldn't have lost Zack Snyder if they did and we would've gotten some epic Superman stories instead of that JL movie that was way too short, way too rushed and put so little studio effort in that DC should've decided then and there to break contract and go their own way as an independant studio, like they're doing with Titans, Doom Patrol and more upcoming DC series (though still sponsored by WB).   WB board should be on their knees sucking/licking every DC employee into climax for that 2nd chance, which they didn't deserve.   The fact they didn't have any hope that DC would best Marvel, despite them making a shit ton more money than Marvel, is utterly disgusting. How can you lose faith in a profitable product and then mess with it so badly you create the worst and smallest of 5 movies (at that time) when it was supposed to be the best and biggest.   I really hope Geoff Johns & co got an apology and I hope even more that Zack got one from each of them and a new offer to return, but I doubt it. People like that hate admitting they were wrong.  But at least we got the real DC back! MoS, (BvS, WW) Aquaman and now Shazam.  BvS and WW had some WB meddling, like certain scenes got cut that should've been there, others got replaced for cheaper shots etc. Which again shows WB's lack of faith in DC movies, back then. But that seems changed now, I hope.

text: (The Second coming of Jesus Christ. This will be a terrible day for those people who are still in their SINS, when Jesus comes back to judge the world in righteousness):    And there shall be signs  in the sun,   and in the moon,   and in the stars;    and upon the earth  distress of nations, with perplexity;    the sea and the waves roaring;    Men's hearts failing them   for fear,  and for looking after those things   which are coming on the earth:    for the powers of heaven   shall be shaken.    (Signs): Jesus shifts his focus to the end times with his second   mention of cosmic turmoil. (Isaiah 21:11)<---And great earthquakes shall be in divers places, and famines, and pestilences; and fearful sights and great signs shall there be from heaven. (Isaiah 24:18-20)<---And it shall come to pass, that he who fleeth from the noise of the fear shall fall into the pit; and he that cometh up out of the midst of the pit shall be taken in the snare: for the windows from on high are open, and the foundations of the earth do shake. The earth is utterly broken down, the earth is clean dissolved, the earth is moved exceedingly. The earth shall reel to and fro like a drunkard, and shall be removed like a cottage; and the transgression thereof shall be heavy upon it; and it shall fall, and not rise again. (Isaiah 34:4)<---And all the host of heaven shall be dissolved, and the heavens shall be rolled together as a scroll: and all their host shall fall down, as the leaf falleth off from the vine, and as a falling fig from the fig tree. (Ezekiel 32:7-8)<---And when I shall put thee out, I will cover the heaven, and make the stars thereof dark; I will cover the sun with a cloud, and the moon shall not give her light. All the bright lights of heaven will I make dark over thee, and set darkness upon thy land, saith the Lord GOD. (Joel 2:30-31)<---And I will shew wonders in the heavens and in the earth, blood, and fire, and pillars of smoke. The sun shall be turned into darkness, and the moon into blood, before the great and the terrible day of the LORD come. (Men's hearts failing them): The terror of cosmic chaos will cause apprehension about what is coming).    And then   shall they see  the Son of man   coming in a cloud    with power   and great glory.    (The Son of Man coming in a cloud): The reference here is to authoritative return of Jesus. The allusion to the cloud and the figure comes from (Daniel 7:13-14)<---I saw in the night visions, and, behold, one like the Son of man came with the clouds of heaven, and came to the Ancient of days, and they brought him near before him. And there was given him dominion, and glory, and a kingdom, that all people, nations, and languages, should serve him: his dominion is an everlasting dominion, which shall not pass away, and his kingdom that which shall not be destroyed. The image of the cloud is important, since God is identified as riding the clouds in the Old Testament. (Exodus 34:5)<---And the LORD descended in the cloud, and stood with him there, and proclaimed the name of the LORD. (Psalms 104:3)<---Who layeth the beams of his chambers in the waters: (((who maketh the clouds his chariot))): who walketh upon the wings of the wind. (With Power and Great Glory): The Son of Man has divine authority to judge the world).    And when these things   (((begin)))   to come to pass,    then look up,   and lift up your heads;    for your redemption   draweth nigh.    (Lift up your heads.....redemption draws near): This is the sign of the deliverance of Jesus followers. The Son of Man acts on behalf of those how have suffered in his name).    (Luke 21:25-28).

text: You know, it's because we settle for average looking movies like this that the studios think they can make something less than sub par and we'd just go to see it because we're fans of the superhero genre. We should be demanding for a better standard of film, especially when it comes to DC who right now have built this universe in which nothing they make seems worthy of any interest. Honestly, if you wanna settle for this fake looking rubber Shazam suit and accept it just because it's coming out then so be it. There's a reason as to why Marvel keep crushing it year after year. It comes from the people themselves and although it goes through Disney, the producers understand the characters and you can see it whenever you watch any of the MCU movies. From the horrible colour grade of Man of Steel, to the CGI mess that is Justice League and all the way down to the studios not understanding the character of Superman, it will never get better if we settle for these sub standard movies.

text: Just so everyone gets the story right, Shazam was originally called Captain Marvel. Billy Batson would say Shazam! and turn into Captain Marvel. Captain Marvel was originally in Fawcett Comics but they were sued by DC claiming Captain Marvel was basically a knockoff of Superman and a 12 year legal battle insued. Fawcett ultimately stopped publication of any Captain Marvel Comics and thus lost the copyright from lack of use. At least one other company tried publishing Captain Marvel Comics but it never lasted long because they didn't sell very well until Marvel Comics published a character called Captain Marvel in the 60s. DC did get the rights to the entire Marvel family but Marvel already held the rights to the name Captain Marvel. Everytime DC used the Captain Marvel name in Shazam they had to pay Marvel since Marvel held the copyright. DC got tired of paying them and more recently changed his name from Captain Marvel to Shazam and the Marvel family to the Shazam family. So Shazam was the FIRST superhero to be called Captain Marvel.

Post credits...brainiac ship is searching for superman as the last kryptonian...because he is the true responsible of krypton's destruction.  The Batman - gotham knight (2013): ten years before the events of man of steel, bruce wayne is in his early career as vigilante as he has already fought normal criminal, now must face the united falcone and maroni crime families as they hired assassin like deadshot, killer croc and deathstroke and also his first encounter with the joker. Mid credits: deadshot and killer croc are in blackgate prison, deathstroke escaped, both are transfered to another prison and their files are with amanda waller so she can formed the task force x (suicide squad). Post credits: flashfoward to present, bruce watches the metropolis invasion and goes to save his employees.  Wonder woman (2014): almost the same plot of the original only that the parts of batman v superman aftermath are omitted. Mid credits - her friends are looking the notes they found of the motherboxes. Post credits- wonder woman is in greece when she see the news of metropolis invasion.  The flash (2014): Months before the events of man of steel, barry allen is caught by a lighting given him superspeed, now with his new power must face villains like abracadabra and captian boomerang. Mid credits: reverse flash sees that barry has achivied in becoming the flash, so he will wait until he is his fully potential so he can kill him. Post credits: captain boomerag is select by the task force x.  Green lantern corps (2014): john stewart is recruited by hal jordan to help him to stop sinestro and his sinestro corps to take the universe. Mid credits: a new enemy the red lanterns appears. Post credits: the guardians of the universe tell the story of the motherboxes.to hal.and stewart.  Batman v superman dawn of justice (2015): after the events of man of steel, batman recluntally team up with superman to take down lex luthor and the joker who are working together. They meet wonder woman too (superman doesnt die and lex is no in jail.because of lack of evidence) post credits: an army of parademons are going to earth comanded by steppenwolf.  Aquaman (2015): mostly the same plot and mid credits  Justice league (2016): when steppenwolf tries to conquer earth and claim the motherboxes, superman, batman, wonder woman, flash, green lantern (john stewart), introducing cyborg and martian manhunter must join forces to save the planet. Mid credits: on apokolips, darkseid recieves the news of his uncle's defeated so he prepares his own invasion to earth, comanded by himself. Post credit: new genesis discovers darkseid's plan so highfather orders orion to he ready.  Man of steel: world's finest (2016): clark is trying to balance his normal and super lives but an unexpected reunion with his cousin kara zor el, they must face the prisioners of the phantom zone as well lex luthor's creation bizarro Mid credits: brainiac has located superman and supergirl, he travels.to earth. Mid credits: batman is designing the watchtower. Post credits: the rise of the league of assasins, talia as her leader and her second in command, the 12 years old damian.  Wonder woman - princess of themyscira (2017): diana faces cheetah on a deadly battle. Mid credits: ares.returns, post credits: diana teaching ancient greece to children.  Suicide squad - hello baby (2017): amanda waller activates the task force x. Mid credits: cadmus operation.  Justice league - the last world (2018): brainiac arrives.to claim.superman and supergirl, but the justice league with new members will.stop him. Mid credits: darkseid is ready.  Flashpoint (2018): when barry discovers reverse flash was his.mother killer, he travels back in time to save her, but after that, everything has changed for bad.  The batman - shatterd family (2018): to stop the league of assassins, batman must face his own family, his lover talia and his son damian. Crossing sides, hadest decision, the batman defining battle. Mid credits: damian becomes.robin  Batman v superman - shadow enemy (2018): batman and superman must stop.cadmus and their clonning expermimens to create.the perfect.soldier. appeareance.of superboy.  Green lantern corps - the corps war (2019).- stewart and hal.are. in the middle.of a. War between red lanterns. Mid credits: the thangarian home planet is attacked by darkseid, hawkgirl.escapes.  Wonder woman - olympus (2019): diana must find the ancient homeworld.of.the greek gods so.she can be sure.about the inminet threat that is coming to earth. text: To be honest, this film looked like trash when I viewed the premier trailer some months ago. However, DC Comics/Warner Bros has done a exceedingly better showcasing of what 'Shazam' will be like at the cinema. It is good to see 'Mr. Chuck Bartowski' (Chuck was such a good program) aka Zachary Levi be a lead actor for a superhero motion picture. I feel that DC Comics is on a bit of a hotstreak with the box office successes of Wonder Woman and Aquaman. DC may have now found a formula that suits their superhero characters like Marvel Comics has found with theirs (I think majority of that stems from Robert Downey Jr's impeccable interpretation of Tony Stark). It is time for DC to 'get in the mix' amongst this superhero motion picture craze before the fizzle becomes flat. The comic book genre (in terms of cinema) is just about at max saturation and sooner than later movie-goers will become disillusioned with these type of films. The potential usage of comedy, action and Zachary's on-screen charisma will possibly bode well for Shazam. Also, having Eminem on the soundtrack is a substantial plus too. I will be viewing this for sure! I am also still patiently waiting for 'Green Lantern Corps' @ DC/Warner Bros. I need that to happen on the silver screen! Ha!

text: Carol Danvers and Mar Vell are imposters, Marvel comic has been known for being lazy when it comes to creativity, the majority of their characters are copied from Detective Comics. Iron-Man is a copy from Batman a rich entrepreneur that fights crime as a super hero, Thanos is a copy from DC Darkseid, Deadpool is a copy from DC Deathstroke, Marvel blackcat a copy from DC Catwoman, Marvel Dr Strange a copy from DC DR Fate, Marvel the Wasp a copy from DC Bumblebee, Marvel Mockingbird copy from DC Black Canary, Marvel Hawkeye copied from DC Green Arrow, Marvel Antman copied from DC The Atom, then you have the female Captain Marvel that copied the name from FAWCETT Comics later purchased by Detective Comics Captain Marvel etc... DC Captain Marvel was created in 1939 by Bill Parker,  while Marvels version Captain Marvel (Carol Danvers) And Mar Vell where created from 1967-1969 this shows you who the real Captain Marvel is. Dates alone shows who came up with the name and Character first and it is not the feminist created by Marvel Comics, Carol Danvers is a crappy character and a copy cat. If you like Marvel Captain Marvel version itâ€™s fine, Iâ€™m not going to fight over some made up cartoons. Iâ€™m just putting historical facts on these creations.

text: Teenager Billy Batson jumps from one foster home to another as he is determined to find his long lost mother after being separated from her as a child. He gets one last chance with Victor and Rosa Vasquez, along with their other adopted kids - Freddy, Mary, Darla, Eugene, and Pedro.  After defending Freddy from some bullies, Billy is summoned to the Rock of Eternity to meet The Wizard, who grants him ancient powers to become the champion Shazam, which turns Billy into an adult superhero. Freddy finds out, and the two decide to have fun being a hero. But The Wizard granted him the powers to stop Dr. Thaddeus Sivana, a man who was almost chosen as a child to inherit the powers before he became corrupted and obsessed with unleashing the Seven Deadly Sins, monstrous creatures that seek to destroy mankind.  The foster kids help Billy locate his mom, Marilyn, but she reveals to him that she essentially abandoned him because she didn't feel ready to care for a child and thought he was better off without her. Meanwhile, Sivana learns Shazam's true identity and holds the kids hostage until Billy decides to give up his powers. However, Billy instead shares the power with the other kids, who all turn into superheroes and fight off the Seven Deadly Sins. They overpower Sivana and remove his powerful eye that gives the Sins freedom, and they are once again imprisoned in the Rock of Eternity.  Billy stays with his new foster family for good, while Sivana meets an alien caterpillar called Mr. Mind in prison, who offers to help him obtain the power he seeks.

text: Ok... I don't have to defend Captain Marvel. It's by far the best CAPTAIN Matvel and doesn't suck like Shazam.  Shazam has horrible casting... Zachary Levi... REALLY???? He was good in Chuck, but sucks for Shazam. The kids are ANNOYING. And the villain is LAME!!!!!  The main character Billy Batson and his Super HERO version Shazam seem like complete opposites. They are the SAME AND YET COMPLETELY DIFFERENT. The acting SUCKED AND VERY WOODEN.   PLOT HOLES, PLOT HOLES, PLOT HOLES  Shazam doesn't know how to use his powers and takes forever to get there, and yet his foster brothers and sisters get the same powers and know how to do everything right pff the bat... Really!!!!?  Shazam just flat out sucked!!!!! The jokes weren't even funny and the only thing I laughed at was the lightning thing, because it was that DUMB!!!!  Everything in Shazam has beem done before and done better in other movies.  The latest DC movies  1. Justice League 2. Suicide Squad 3. Man of Steel 4. The Dark Knight Rises 5. Aquaman 6. Batman Begins 7. Batman vs Superman 8. Wonder Woman 9. The Dark Knight 10. Shazam  Anybody that argues that Batman vs Suoerman or Justice League are worse than Shazam..... Ummmm Shazam is boring, lame, not funny and horrible casting and BM vs SM and JL were exciting, action packed, great casting for Suoerman, Aquaman, Wonderman and yes Ben Affleck makes a waaaay better Batma. Than Zachery Levi makes as Shazam.
